%% Diagram: Browser-side violation reporting paths
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Page as Page<br/>(CSP enforced)
    participant Doc as Document<br/>(securitypolicyviolation event)
    participant UA as User-Agent<br/>Reporting Queue
    participant Legacy as Legacy endpoint<br/>(report-uri)
    participant Modern as Modern endpoint<br/>(Reporting-Endpoints)

    Note over Page: A directive is violated<br/>(blocked-uri, inline, eval, ...)
    Page->>Doc: fire SecurityPolicyViolationEvent
    Note over Doc: In-page handler can<br/>capture, sample, log
    alt report-to directive present (Chromium)
        Page->>UA: queue report (type=csp-violation)
        UA-->>Modern: POST application/reports+json<br/>credentials: same-origin<br/>(may batch)
        Modern-->>UA: 2xx OK / 410 Remove Endpoint
    else report-uri only (Firefox, Safari)
        Page-->>Legacy: POST application/csp-report<br/>(deprecated body, one report per POST)
    end
    Note over UA,Modern: Out-of-band, best-effort,<br/>retried by the user agent
